29. Q: What are the three types of bugs and what is an example of each? Which debugging methods would you try for each one? [Thursday notes](http://chuckvose.com/exercises/session2/week1/thursday.html)

A:

unexpected end of input- a block has not been closed, check that there is an "end" for every method or conditional call
nil:nilClass- an object is being called which is not yet defined, check for variables or methods which need to have values placed
Argument is not numeric (ArgumentError)- You are trying to invoke a method meant for a numberic object on a non-numeric object, if require numeric change to numeric using .to_i or .to_f,




